ts, Yuan drama formed a vital part of China's culture of performance and entertainment in the thirteenth and fourteenth centuries.To date, few Yuan-dynasty plays have been translated into English. Well-known translators and scholars have supervised the making of this collection and add a short description to each play. A general introduction situates all selections within their cultural and historical contexts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aChinese dramayYuan dynasty, 1260-1368vTranslations into English. 7aDRAMA / Asian / General.2bisacsh1 aCavanaugh, Jerome, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChaves, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColeman, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHargett, James M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHegel, Robert E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHessney, Richard C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHsia, C. T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHsia, C. T., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHuang, Pi-Twan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKao, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKao, George, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLai, Kuan-Fook, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLi, Wai-Yee, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLi, Wai-yee, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMing, Wang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShen, Gloria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabul